name: Boeing 747-4H6LCF "Dreamlifter" [N718BA] Wet Arrival at Paine Field ᴴᴰ
description:
One of the more common, but always impressive visitors to Paine Field is Boeing's 4-strong fleet of 747-400LCF (Large Cargo Freighter) aircraft, which ship 787 Dreamliner parts around the globe for manufacture in Everett and Charleston, where 787s are put together. Here we have N718BA, a former Malaysia Airlines aircraft, landing on runway 16R and taxiing into the Dreamlifter unloading facility, taken from the fantastic viewing deck at Boeing's Future of Flight facility. Enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
